Petroplus Holdings Disclosure of Shareholdings | Business Wire


























































Petroplus Holdings Disclosure of Shareholdings






November 10, 2008 01:19 PM Eastern Standard Time



ZUG, Switzerland--(BUSINESS WIRE)--Regulatory News:
    

      Petroplus Holdings AG (SWX:PPHN), in accordance with Art. 20 of the 
      Federal Act on Stock Exchanges and Securities Trading, received on 
      November 10, 2008 the following information from shareholders:
    

      Chilton Investment Company, LLC located at 1266 East Main Street, 7th 
      Floor, Stamford, CT, 06902, USA, (contact James Steinthal) reduced their 
      ownership interest through their funds and managed accounts, below 3% of 
      registered shares of Petroplus Holdings AG due to a sale of shares on 
      November 3rd, 2008.
    

      Chilton Investment Company, LLC, as a General Partner and Investment 
      Manager to the entities listed as follows control the shares of 
      Petroplus Holdings AG: Chilton International, L.P. (BVI) – 
      Maples Finance BVI Ltd., Tortola, British Virgin Islands; Chilton 
      Investment Partners, L.P. (US), Stamford, USA; Wilshire Chilton 
      Long/Short Segregated Portfolio (Cayman) – c/o 
      Wilshire Institutional Master Fund, c/o Walkers SPV Limited, Grand 
      Cayman, Cayman Islands; Chilton ERISA International, L.P. (BVI) – 
      Maples Finance BVI Ltd., Tortola, British Virgin Islands; Lyxor/Chilton 
      International Fund Ltd. (Jersey), Channel Islands; Chilton Opportunity 
      International, L.P. (BVI) – Maples Finance BVI 
      Ltd., Tortola, British Virgin Islands; Chilton Global Partners, L.P. 
      (US), Stamford, USA; Chilton Opportunity Trust, L.P. (US), Stamford, 
      USA; Chilton Strategic Value Partners, L.P. (US), Stamford, USA; K2 Long 
      Alpha Master Fund, L.P. (US), Stamford, USA; Chilton European 
      LiquidFund, L.P. (Cayman), c/o M&C Corporate Services Limited, Grand 
      Cayman, Cayman Islands; Chilton QP European Partners, L.P. (US), 
      Stamford, USA; Chilton Europe MAP Fund Ltd. (Cayman), c/o Merrill Lynch 
      Alternative Investments, LLC, New York, USA; Chilton European 
      International, L.P. (BVI) - Maples Finance BVI Ltd., Tortola, British 
      Virgin Islands; Chilton Global Natural Resources Partners, L.P. (US), 
      Stamford, USA.
    

      Petroplus Holdings AG is the largest independent refiner and wholesaler 
      of petroleum products in Europe. Petroplus focuses on refining and 
      currently owns and operates seven refineries across Europe: the Coryton 
      refinery on the Thames Estuary in the United Kingdom, the Ingolstadt 
      refinery in Ingolstadt, Germany, the Belgium Refining Company refinery 
      in Antwerp, Belgium, the Petit Couronne refinery in Petit Couronne, 
      France, the Cressier refinery in the canton of Neuchâtel, Switzerland, 
      the Reichstett refinery in Alsace, France and the Teesside refinery in 
      Teesside, United Kingdom. The refineries have a combined throughput 
      capacity of approximately 864,000 bpd.
    




