 Career History



Fund Advisor

                                    Tenure Unconfirmed                


Chilton Investment Services LLC


                  Chilton Investment Services (CIS) generally invests client accounts in publicly-traded, liquid equity securities or municipal, corporate, governmental or high-yield bonds or other fixed income instruments. For some accounts, investments may also include debt securities, derivatives and other obligations and instruments. In addition, some accounts invest in pooled investment vehicles (hedge funds) which are managed by external investment managers.                




Fund Advisor

                                    Tenure Unconfirmed                


Chilton Investment Company LLC


                  Chilton Investment Co. manages numerous strategies across various sectors globally and across various products such as equity, debt and quantitative methods. The firm's equity investment approach involves value-oriented, fundamental research and disciplined portfolio management. They diversify equities strategies to encompass a global approach focusing on Pan-Asia and Europe. This includes a variety of market segments such as the energy, technology, financial and consumer sectors. To take advantage of unique crossover investment opportunities, Chilton employs a global distressed opportunities strategy. Their approach to debt utilizes fundamental, detailed research on debt instruments of distressed companies. Chilton uses a quantitative model to invest across a variety of alternative strategies. This model attempts to optimize returns and minimize both volatility and correlation.                





